{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "e373bcb8-30a0-49e3-b116-ed018b146c9e",
    "name": "rent-nest-backend",
    "description": "RentNest — rental property marketplace REST API.\n\n**Auth:** login (or register) first; the API sets httpOnly `accessToken`/`refreshToken` cookies which Postman sends automatically on subsequent requests. Alternatively, copy `data.accessToken` from the login response into an `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header (the raw token without `Bearer` also works).\n\n**Roles:** TENANT (rentals, payments, reviews), LANDLORD (properties, request approval), ADMIN (categories, user management). Admin credentials: `admin@rentnest.com` / `admin123`.\n\n**Response envelope:** success → `{ success, message, data, meta? }`; error → `{ success, message, errorDetails }`.\n\n**Payment flow:** tenant submits rental request → landlord approves → tenant calls `payments/create` and pays via the returned Stripe Checkout `checkoutUrl` (test card 4242 4242 4242 4242) → Stripe webhook activates the rental → landlord completes it → tenant can review.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "31457961"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "devBaseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
